  "texts": [
    "These data, primarily collected by meteorological institutions, can be limited by spatial coverage and temporal resolution.",
    "Satellite imagery presents a valuable supplement, offering real-time, high-resolution data for a wide range of climate and environmental variables 47, 285.",
    "Previous studies have shown the potential of integrating satellite data into disease surveillance and forecasting models, utilizing purely AI approaches [286] [287] [288].",
    "This highlights the ability of AI to extract rich information from satellite data, enabling mechanistic models to build more comprehensive and dynamic representations of abiotic and biotic drivers of disease transmission.",
    "Third, disease transmission is a complex process influenced by a confluence of epidemiological, biological, and socio-behavioral factors."
